iscussion about the ways in which these beliefs develop and situates the findings within the wider field of teacher efficacy research. It helps further understanding of factors that may influence teacher self-efficacy and suggests new directions for research to explore in future studies. It will appeal to postgraduates and researchers with an interest in language teacher cognition, the psychology of language teaching and those in the wider fields of self-efficacy, teacher efficacy and teacher agency. It is also of use to those with an interest in the high school English education system in Japan, as well as researchers investigating similar contexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teaching (Higher)xJapanese speakers. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teaching (Higher)zJapan. 0aSecond language acquisitionxStudy and teachingzJapan. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aJapanese high school teachers of languages.  alanguage acquisition.  alanguage teacher cognition.  alanguage teacher efficacy.  alanguage teacher self-efficacy.  apsychology of language teaching.  aself-efficacy beliefs.  ateacher agency.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020 Englishz978311070476108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020z9783110704563oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068960008iTitle is part of eBook package: